More than 176 teams drawn from the six wards of the Kilgoris constituency took part in the preliminaries that started in OctoberThe winners at the ward level pocketed Sh20,000 and a trophy each while the runners-ups walked with Sh15,000Tasur said that he will sponsor best teams from the wards in the FKF sub branch league Twenty-eight teams have qualified for the second round of the Joel Tasur Peace youth football tournament slated for early this year.
More than 176 teams drawn from the six wards of the Kilgoris constituency took part in the preliminaries that started in October.
Angate were the Kapsinendet winners while Red Eagles won in Lolgorian ward. Other ward winners were Tigers (Shankoe ward), Tumpelian (Kimintet), Olowang and Romosha (both from Kilgoris Central).



