The event mostly targeted the rival Maasai, Kipsigis, Kisii and Kuria communities who have been engaging in cattle rustling, land disputes among other cross border conflicts.
“Such sporting activities would offer a platform to the local youths from the various ethnic backgrounds to interact and share their diverse cultural beliefs so as to become tolerant to each other,” said Tasur. According to family members, the deceased was attached to the DP’s security detail for several years. The footbridge was damaged by a trailer carrying an excavator earlier in December 2020. However they made us feel, the men and women in this list elicited different emotions in all of us.